cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper addresses the problem of robustly training a ConvNet for regression, which is a common task in computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel optimization algorithm that involves unsupervised detection of outliers, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on facial and fashion landmark detection, age and head pose estimation, which are all tasks related to multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper uses a Gaussian-uniform mixture model, which is a statistical technique commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE).
